        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 1 at 11:24PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 1124 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northeast of Agua Nueva, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Rafael Ranch Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
